  "text": "Sample preparation for serum free isoprostanes. We used a slightly modified solid phase extraction described by Zhao et al. [CITATION_1] . Briefly, aliquots of serum (0.5 ml) were transferred to tubes containing butylated hydroxytoluene (BHT) at a final concentration of 20 mM and d 4 -iPF 2a -III and d 4 -iPF 2a -VI (1 ng as the internal standards) were added to each sample. Each sample was acidified with 1 ml of 1 N HCl and 2 ml of 100 mM formate buffer (pH 3.0), and centrifuged at 2000 g for 10 min and the supernatant submitted to solid-phase extraction.",
